featured_reviews.review_id:
Mohammed Appa Dargah is  one of the most renowned Sufi pilgrim centers in Kanyakumari, the southernmost district of Tamil Nadu. It is located in Thuckalay and was dedicated to a Sufi saint Peer Mohammed Sahib who was also a Tamil poet. The vow of sleeping in the Dargah premises is considered sacred.

Thuckalay or Thakkalai is a town in Kanyakumari district of Tamil Nadu, India. Thuckalay comes under the Padmanabhapuram Municipality, and is the administrative headquarters of Kalkulam Taluk. The Revenue Divisional Office is located in Mettukadai

featured_reviews.review_id: one sunny day i travelled from tvm to thuckalay peer mohammed appa dargah in my two wheeler. Vey hot sun and was tired. Like always, the dargah offered a shelter from difficulties.The dagah is very serene and calm. We generally offer flowers to the saint. The tomb was in the open air and a meditation hall is there adjoining to the tomb. I sat there for about an hour. Like always i could feel the energy entering me. I got relaxed completely. The water from the dargah dipped with fresh jasmin flowers offered to the saint was   felt like amrit
